---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro'
---

<SiteLayout title="About" description="About.">
  <article class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-3xl flex-col">
    <header class="border-b border-border/70 pb-8">
      <h1
        class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-foreground md:text-[3rem] md:leading-[1.08]"
        data-i18n="about_title"
      >
        About.
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-[1.04rem] leading-8 text-muted-foreground">
      <p data-i18n="about_body_1">
        This blog keeps notes on frontend implementation, interface structure, and the work of
        making screens easier to read.
      </p>
      <p data-i18n="about_body_2">
        The point is not volume. It is to keep the decisions that survived real work and quiet
        iteration.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
